    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{t^{2}+3}{t^{2}-t}-\frac{t-3}{t}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{4}{t-1}, t\ne 0</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{t^{2}+3}{t^{2}-t}-\frac{t-3}{t}} 
      \amp = {\frac{t^{2}+3}{t\mathopen{}\left(t-1\right)}-\frac{t-3}{t}}  \\
      \amp = {\frac{t^{2}+3}{t\mathopen{}\left(t-1\right)}-\frac{t-3}{t}} \cdot \frac{(t - 1)}{(t - 1)} \\
      \amp = {\frac{t^{2}+3}{t\mathopen{}\left(t-1\right)}-\frac{\left(t-3\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-1\right)}{t\mathopen{}\left(t-1\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{t^{2}+3-\left(t-3\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-1\right)}{t\mathopen{}\left(t-1\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{t^{2}+3-\left(t^{2}-4t+3\right)}{t\mathopen{}\left(t-1\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{t^{2}+3-t^{2}+4t-3}{t\mathopen{}\left(t-1\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{4t}{t\mathopen{}\left(t-1\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{4}{t-1}, t\ne 0}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>{t}</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>t \ne {0}</m>.</p>
</solution>
